description: From French bohémien (“person from Bohemia”), from Bohême (“Bohemia”).

adjectives.description: bohemian (comparative more bohemian, superlative most bohemian)

entries.meaning: Unconventional, especially in habit or dress.
examples: Please tell me you're not one of Toulouse's oh-so-talented, charmingly bohemian, tragically impoverished protégés! -Nicole Kidman, Moulin Rouge!

entries.meaning: An unconventional or nonconformist artist or writer.
